Package org.forgerock.openam.core.rest.authn.callbackhandlers

Interface JsonCallbackParser<T extends Callback>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - A class which implements the Callback interface.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RestAuthCallbackHandler<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRestAuthCallbackHandler, RestAuthChoiceCallbackHandler, RestAuthConfirmationCallbackHandler, RestAuthHiddenValueCallbackHandler, RestAuthHttpCallbackHandler, RestAuthLanguageCallbackHandler, RestAuthNameCallbackHandler, RestAuthNameValueOutputCallbackHandler, RestAuthPasswordCallbackHandler, RestAuthPollingWaitCallbackHandler, RestAuthRedirectCallbackHandler, RestAuthTextInputCallbackHandler, RestAuthTextOutputCallbackHandler, RestAuthX509CallbackHandler
    public interface JsonCallbackParser<T extends Callback>
    Implementations of this interface define how to convert a Callback into and from a JSON representation. See the javadoc for the convertToJson method for details on the required JSON representation.

    • Method Detail

      • getCallbackClassName

        String getCallbackClassName()
        Returns the class name of the Callback the implementation of this interface is for. Should only return the simple name of the class not the FQDN.
        Returns:
        The name of the class this parser is for.

      • convertToJson

        org.forgerock.json.JsonValue convertToJson​(T callback,
                                           int index)
                                    throws RestAuthException
        Converts the given Callback into JSON format. The JSON representation of the Callback MUST be in the following form:

        { type : "NameCallback", output : [ { name : "prompt", value : "Enter User Name:" } ], input : [ { key : "name", value : "" } ] }

        The type field MUST be the name of the Callback class. Output fields detail information that the client can use to display to the user. Input fields detail information that need to be complete before the callbacks is submitted.
        Parameters:
        callback - The Callback to convert to JSON.
        index - the position of this callback in the returned structure.
        Returns:
        The JSON representation of the Callback.
        Throws:
        RestAuthException

      • convertFromJson

        T convertFromJson​(T callback,
                  org.forgerock.json.JsonValue jsonObject)
           throws RestAuthException
        Converts the JSONObject into a Callback, setting the values set in the JSONObject onto the given Callback. Method must set the appropriate values on the Callback parameter and return the same Callback parameter. This is required because of the way the AuthContext handles submitting requirements (Callbacks).
        Parameters:
        callback - The Callback to set values from the JSONObject onto.
        jsonObject - The JSON representation of the Callback.
        Returns:
        The same Callback as in the parameters with the required values set.
        Throws:
        RestAuthException
